> @datumbox The implementation is much similar to detectron2. We use the tricks as descibed as the original paper:
> 
> * add the centerness brach on the regression branch instead of classification branch;
> * center sampling strategy (radis = 1.5);
> * use GIoU loss for the regression loss;
> * normalize the regression targets by the stride of feature map, but do not use `Scale` layer on the regression branch;
> 
> there is also three minor difference compared to the offical implementation ([AdelaiDet](https://github.com/aim-uofa/AdelaiDet)):
> 
> * normalize the regression loss  by the number of positive sample (similar to other losses) instead of sum of ctrness_targets;
> * use the square root of the multiplication of classification score and centerness to threshold, instead of classification score. so the score_thresh is much greater than normal setting (0.2 vs 0.05).
> * the nms thresh is 0.5 as normal instead of 0.6 used in paper.
> 
> But I think they has negligible influence on the detection result.
> 
> When you are free, you can check them.

