Note that it's often cleaner to define internal ("private") variables as class extension properties, e.g.
```
@interface TCSoundClassifierPreprocessing ()
@property (nonatomic) PowerSpectrum *powerSpectrum;
@property (nonatomic) MelFrequenceFilterPank *melFilterBank;
@end
```
This will auto-synthesize underlying instance variables such as `_powerSpectrum` and allow you to use property syntax (e.g. `self.powerSpectrum`) outside of the initializer

