Power-up state functions uses varargs in the C API, so they will require a special case. Think of them as getting/setting either an array of (channel, state) tuples or parallel arrays of channels and states.

I think the way you call them in C is something like this:
```
int32 states[4];
DAQmxGetDigitalPowerUpStates("Dev1", "port0/line0", &states[0], "port0/line1", &states[1], "port0/line2", &states[2], "port0/line3", &states[3], (const char*)NULL);
DAQmxSetDigitalPowerUpStates("Dev1", "port0/line0", states[0], "port0/line1", states[1], "port0/line2", states[2], "port0/line3", states[3], (const char*)NULL);
```

